## Adding Viscose

Viscose should be added as a separate benchmark pack.

Required files:

```txt
src/engine/benchmarks/viscose/
  index.ts
  viscosePack.ts
  viscoseScenarios.ts
  viscoseRanks.ts
  viscoseThresholds.ts
  viscoseCategoryMap.ts
```

The Viscose pack should define:

- Viscose benchmark ID
- Viscose rank names
- Viscose rank order
- Viscose scenarios
- Viscose categories
- Viscose thresholds
- Viscose platform support
- Viscose benchmark version
- Source notes for where the data came from

If some Viscose data is missing, the pack should still exist but mark those scenarios as progress-only.

---

## Custom Benchmark Packs

Later, the app should support user-created custom benchmark packs.

Custom packs should allow users to define:

- Custom benchmark name
- Custom categories
- Custom scenarios
- Optional score thresholds
- Optional rank system
- Universal category mapping

This makes the app future-proof.

A custom benchmark without thresholds still works as a progress tracker.

A custom benchmark with thresholds works as a rank tracker.

