## Codex Build Instructions

Use this instruction when asking Codex to build the system:

```txt
Build the Aim Brain Engine as a benchmark-agnostic TypeScript logic layer.

Do not hardcode Voltaic into the core engine.

Create a benchmark pack system where Voltaic, Viscose, Custom, and future benchmarks are separate packs.

The core engine should handle score stats, trends, consistency, weakness detection, recommendations, and coach summaries.

Benchmark packs should provide scenario lists, aliases, native categories, universal category mappings, rank names, score thresholds, platform support, benchmark version metadata, and data source notes.

Add a shared BenchmarkPack interface and make each benchmark pack follow it.

Support missing threshold data with a progress-only fallback.

Never invent rank conversion for scenarios without threshold data.

Add UI support for Benchmark Mode, Universal Aim Mode, and Comparison Mode.

Add tests with sample Voltaic and Viscose data to confirm that the same engine can analyze both benchmark packs.
```

